of 80 to attend public school.

61
00:08:11,641 --> 00:08:15,854
Mrs Gump, he's going to have
to go to a special school.

62
00:08:15,979 --> 00:08:20,734
- He'll be just fine.
- What does normal mean anyway?

63
00:08:20,859 --> 00:08:26,073
He might be a bit on the slow side,
but my boy Forrest

64
00:08:26,198 --> 00:08:29,368
will get the same opportunities
as everyone else.

65
00:08:29,493 --> 00:08:33,747
He's not going to some special school
to learn how to retread tyres.

66
00:08:33,872 --> 00:08:37,334
We're talking about
five little points here.

67
00:08:38,669 --> 00:08:41,546
There must be something can be done.

68
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:45,842
We're a progressive school system.

69
00:08:46,301 --> 00:08:49,388
We don't want to see
anybody left behind.

70
00:08:49,513 --> 00:08:54,184
Is there a Mr Gump, Mrs Gump?

71
00:08:56,812 --> 00:08:58,981
He's on vacation.

72
00:09:15,664 --> 00:09:20,043
Your mama sure does care
about your schooling, son.

73
00:09:25,257 --> 00:09:27,801
You don't say much, do you?

74
00:09:39,604 --> 00:09:44,359
"Finally, he had to try.
It looked easy, but...

75
00:09:44,484 --> 00:09:46,945
"Oh, what happened. First they..."

76
00:09:47,070 --> 00:09:51,575
- Mama, what's vacation mean?
- Vacation?

77
00:09:51,700 --> 00:09:54,453
Where daddy went?

78
00:09:56,204 --> 00:10:02,210
Vacation's when you go somewhere...
and you don't ever come back.

79
00:10:06,882 --> 00:10:11,511
Anyway, I guess you could say
me and Mama was on our own.

80
00:10:11,678 --> 00:10:15,974
But we didn't mind.
Our house was never empty.

81
00:10:16,099 --> 00:10:18,977
There was always
folks coming and going.

82
00:10:19,102 --> 00:10:23,732
- Supper! It's supper, everyone!
- That sure looks special.

83
00:10:23,857 --> 00:10:26,318
Sometimes, we had so many people
staying with us

84
00:10:26,443 --> 00:10:29,738
that every room was filled,
with travellers, you know,

85
00:10:29,863 --> 00:10:35,744
folks living out of their suitcases
and hat cases and sample cases.

86
00:10:35,869 --> 00:10:39,915
Forrest Gump,
it's suppertime! Forrest?

87
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:45,462
One time, a young man was staying
with us, and he had a guitar case.

88
00:10:59,643 --> 00:11:03,563
Forrest, I told you not to bother
this nice young man.

89
00:11:03,689 --> 00:11:05,190
No, that's all right, ma'am.

90
00:11:05,315 --> 00:11:08,694
I was showing him
a thing or two on the guitar.

91
00:11:08,819 --> 00:11:11,697
All right. Supper's ready
if y'all want to eat.

92
00:11:11,822 --> 00:11:14,700
Yeah, that sounds good.
Thank you, ma'am.

93
00:11:14,825 --> 00:11:20,247
Say, show me that craZy little walk
you did there. Slow it down some.

94
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:26,461
I liked that guitar. It sounded good.

95
00:11:27,754 --> 00:11:34,469
I started moving around to the music,
swinging my hips.

96
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:40,350
This one night,
me and Mama was out shopping,

97
00:11:40,475 --> 00:11:43,729
and we walked by Benson's furniture
and appliance store, and guess what?

98
00:11:57,075 --> 00:11:59,911
This is not for children's eyes.

99
00:12:02,289 --> 00:12:06,543
Some years later, that handsome
young man who they called The King,

100
00:12:06,668 --> 00:12:09,504
well, he sung too many songs.

101
00:12:09,629 --> 00:12:12,591
Had himself a heart attack
or something.

102
00:12:12,716 --> 00:12:15,635
It must be hard being a king.

103
00:12:19,222 --> 00:12:21,892
It's funny how you remember some
things, but some things you can't.

104
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:28,523
- You do your very best now, Forrest.
- I sure will, Mama.

105
00:12:28,649 --> 00:12:33,570
I remember the bus ride
on the first day of school very well.

106
00:12:36,657 --> 00:12:38,533
Are you coming along?

107
00:12:38,659 --> 00:12:42,079
Mama said not to take rides
from strangers.

108
00:12:42,204 --> 00:12:44,164
This is the bus to school.

109
00:12:47,209 --> 00:12:52,339
- I'm Forrest, Forrest Gump.
- I'm Dorothy Harris.

110
00:12:52,464 --> 00:12:54,675
Well, now we ain't strangers anymore.

111
00:13:07,813 --> 00:13:10,273
This seat's taken.

112
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:13,777
It's taken.

113
00:13:21,243 --> 00:13:23,120
You can't sit here.

114
00:13:25,622 --> 00:13:28,917
You know, it's funny what
a young man recollects,

115
00:13:29,042 --> 00:13:31,795
'cause I don't remember being born.

116
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:34,965
I don't recall what I got
for my first Christmas,

117
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:38,760
and I don't know when I went
on my first outdoor picnic,

118
00:13:38,885 --> 00:13:42,806
but I do remember
the first time I heard

119
00:13:42,931 --> 00:13:46,393
the sweetest voice in the wide world.

120
00:13:46,518 --> 00:13:49,438
You can sit here if you want.

121
00:13:51,648 --> 00:13:55,986
I had never seen anything
so beautiful in my life.

122
00:13:56,153 --> 00:13:58,238
She was like an angel.

123
00:13:58,363 --> 00:14:01,700
Well, are you going
to sit down or aren't you?

124
00:14:06,246 --> 00:14:08,206
What's wrong with your legs?

125
00:14:08,332 --> 00:14:13,128
Nothing at all, thank you.
My legs are just fine and dandy.

126
00:14:13,253 --> 00:14:16,131
I just sat next to her on that bus

127
00:14:16,256 --> 00:14:19,092
and had a conversation
all the way to school.

128
00:14:19,217 --> 00:14:21,511
My back's crooked
like a question mark.

129
00:14:21,636 --> 00:14:26,683
Next to Mama, no one ever talked
to me or asked me questions.

130
00:14:26,808 --> 00:14:29,102
Are you stupid or something?

131
00:14:29,227 --> 00:14:32,731
Mama says,
"Stupid is as stupid does."

132
00:14:32,856 --> 00:14:37,903
- I'm Jenny.
- I'm Forrest, Forrest Gump.

133
00:14:38,028 --> 00:14:40,739
From that day on,
we was always together.

134
00:14:40,864 --> 00:14:43,533
Jenny and me
was like peas and carrots.

135
00:14:46,244 --> 00:14:48,538
She taught me how to climb.

136
00:14:48,664 --> 00:14:51,041
Come on, Forrest, you can do it.

137
00:14:51,166 --> 00:14:53,710
I showed her how to dangle.

138
00:14:55,545 --> 00:15:00,884
She helped me learn how to read,
and I showed her how to swing.

139
00:15:02,302 --> 00:15:07,015
Sometimes, we'd just sit out
and wait for the stars.

140
00:15:07,140 --> 00:15:12,479
- Mama's going to worry about me.
- Just stay a little longer.

141
00:15:12,562 --> 00:15:16,608
For some reason,
Jenny never wanted to go home.

142
00:15:16,733 --> 00:15:19,403
OK, Jenny, I'll stay.

143
00:15:19,528 --> 00:15:22,948
She was my most special friend.

144
00:15:26,159 --> 00:15:28,829
My only friend.

145
00:15:30,580 --> 00:15:34,418
My Mama always told me
that miracles happen every day.

146
00:15:34,543 --> 00:15:38,213
Some people don't think so,
but they do.

147
00:15:40,465 --> 00:15:43,427
Hey, dummy!

148
00:15:43,677 --> 00:15:46,013
Are you retarded,
or just plain stupid?

149
00:15:46,138 --> 00:15:49,391
- Look, I'm Forrest Gimp.
- Just run away, Forrest.

150
00:15:50,809 --> 00:15:53,729
Run, Forrest! Run away! Hurry!

151
00:15:54,021 --> 00:15:57,316
- Get the bikes!
- Let's get him! Come on!

152
00:15:57,441 --> 00:16:02,154
Look out, dummy!
We're going to get you!

153
00:16:02,279 --> 00:16:06,491
Run, Forrest, run! Run, Forrest!

154
00:16:07,951 --> 00:16:10,287
Come back here, you!

155
00:16:23,759 --> 00:16:27,554
Run, Forrest! Run!

156
00:16:58,251 --> 00:17:01,880
You wouldn't
believe it if I told you,

157
00:17:02,005 --> 00:17:05,342
but I can run like the wind blows.

158
00:17:08,637 --> 00:17:14,601
From that day on, if I was
going somewhere, I was running.

159
00:17:47,426 --> 00:17:50,637
That boy sure is a running fool.

160
00:17:54,516 --> 00:17:58,478
Remember how I told you that Jenny
never seemed to want to go home?

161
00:17:58,603 --> 00:18:02,107
She lived in a house
that was as old as Alabama.

162
00:18:02,232 --> 00:18:04,735
Her mama had gone to heaven
when she was five,

163
00:18:04,860 --> 00:18:09,364
and her daddy was
some kind of a farmer.

164
00:18:09,489 --> 00:18:11,325
Jenny?

165
00:18:11,450 --> 00:18:13,452
He was a very loving man.

166
00:18:13,577 --> 00:18:17,831
He was always kissing
and touching her and her sisters.

167
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:24,504
And then this one time, Jenny
wasn't on the bus to go to school.

168
00:18:24,629 --> 00:18:27,090
Jenny,
why didn't you come to school today?

169
00:18:28,091 --> 00:18:29,968
Daddy's taking a nap.

170
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:33,096
Come on!

171
00:18:33,889 --> 00:18:39,436
Jenny, where'd you run to?
You better get back here, girl!

172
00:18:41,021 --> 00:18:43,398
Where you at?

173
00:18:46,234 --> 00:18:49,655
Jenny! Jenny, where you at?

174
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:56,703
Pray with me, Forrest. Pray with me.

175
00:18:58,246 --> 00:19:03,460
Dear God, make me a bird so I can fly
far, far, far away from here.

176
00:19:03,585 --> 00:19:08,465
Dear God, make me a bird
so I can fly far...

177
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:11,426
Mama always said God is mysterious.

178
00:19:13,178 --> 00:19:15,681
He didn't turn Jenny
into a bird that day.

179
00:19:15,806 --> 00:19:19,518
Instead, he had the police say

180
00:19:19,643 --> 00:19:23,146
Jenny didn't have to stay
in that house no more.

181
00:19:23,271 --> 00:19:27,526
She was to live with her grandma,
just over on Creekmore Avenue,

182
00:19:27,651 --> 00:19:31,613
which made me happy,
'cause she was so close.

183
00:19:33,073 --> 00:19:38,537
Some nights, Jenny'd sneak out
and come on over to my house,

184
00:19:38,662 --> 00:19:44,292
Just 'cause she said she was scared.
Scared of what, I don't know.

185
00:19:44,418 --> 00:19:49,923
But I think it was her grandma's dog.
He was a mean dog.

186
00:19:50,173 --> 00:19:54,970
Anyway, Jenny and me was best friends
all the way up through high school.

187
00:19:56,138 --> 00:19:58,849
- Hey, stupid!
- Quit it!

188
00:19:59,433 --> 00:20:00,809
Run, Forrest, run!

189
00:20:00,934 --> 00:20:05,522
- Didn't you hear me, stupid?
- Run, Forrest!

190
00:20:05,647 --> 00:20:10,193
Get in the truck!
Come on! He's getting away! Move it!

191
00:20:10,319 --> 00:20:12,696
Run, Forrest! Run!

192
00:20:40,474 --> 00:20:42,893
Run, Forrest!

193
00:20:45,103 --> 00:20:49,483
Now, it used to be
I ran to get where I was going.

194
00:20:49,608 --> 00:20:53,028
I never thought
it would take me anywhere.

195
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,684
Who in the hell is that?

196
00:21:23,809 --> 00:21:28,605
That is Forrest Gump, coach.
Just a local idiot.

197
00:21:28,772 --> 00:21:33,986
And can you believe it?
I got to go to college, too.

198
00:21:39,616 --> 00:21:43,161
- Forrest, move it! Run!
- OK!

199
00:21:43,286 --> 00:21:47,165
- Run!
- Run, you stupid son of a bitch!

200
00:22:00,053 --> 00:22:02,889
Run, son of a bitch, run! Go! Run!

201
00:22:19,239 --> 00:22:24,453
He must be the stupidest son of
a bitch alive, but he sure is fast.

202
00:22:27,539 --> 00:22:32,586
Now, maybe it's just me,
but college was very confusing times.

203
