- Which way?

934
01:33:30,260 --> 01:33:32,763
Over there! They're over there!

935
01:33:32,888 --> 01:33:37,684
- Get on the wheel and take a left.
- OK.

936
01:33:39,102 --> 01:33:43,482
Gump, what are you doing?
Take a left! Left!

937
01:33:45,359 --> 01:33:49,404
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

938
01:33:50,364 --> 01:33:52,324
That's where we'll find them.

939
01:34:04,962 --> 01:34:08,840
- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.
- OK, so I was wrong.

940
01:34:08,966 --> 01:34:11,843
How are we going to find them?

941
01:34:11,969 --> 01:34:15,722
Maybe you should
Just pray for shrimp.

942
01:34:22,145 --> 01:34:24,648
So I went to church every Sunday.

943
01:34:26,191 --> 01:34:31,905
Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came too,
though he left the praying up to me.

944
01:34:46,628 --> 01:34:51,967
- No shrimp.
- Where the hell's this God of yours?

945
01:34:52,050 --> 01:34:57,055
It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that,
'cause right then God showed up.

946
01:35:14,031 --> 01:35:16,491
You'll never sink this boat!

947
01:35:16,617 --> 01:35:22,706
Now, me, I was scared,
but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.

948
01:35:22,831 --> 01:35:25,208
Come on!

949
01:35:27,210 --> 01:35:33,050
You call this a storm?
Come on, you son of a bitch!

950
01:35:34,926 --> 01:35:42,392
It's time for a showdown! You and me!
I'm right here! Come and get me!

951
01:35:44,686 --> 01:35:48,440
You'll never sink this boat!

952
01:35:50,734 --> 01:35:52,736
Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,

953
01:35:52,861 --> 01:35:54,988
destroying nearly everything
in its path.

954
01:35:55,113 --> 01:35:57,991
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

955
01:35:58,116 --> 01:36:00,619
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

956
01:36:00,744 --> 01:36:05,916
has fallen victim to Carmen
and has been left in utter ruin.

957
01:36:06,041 --> 01:36:07,584
This reporter has learned,

958
01:36:07,709 --> 01:36:11,505
in fact, only one shrimping boat
actually survived the storm.

959
01:36:11,630 --> 01:36:14,049
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

960
01:36:14,174 --> 01:36:17,219
After that, shrimping was easy.

961
01:36:23,058 --> 01:36:26,019
Since people still needed
them shrimps for shrimp cocktails

962
01:36:26,144 --> 01:36:30,440
and barbecues and all, and we were
the only boat left standing,

963
01:36:30,565 --> 01:36:35,904
Bubba-Gump shrimp's what they got.
We got a whole bunch of boats.

964
01:36:36,029 --> 01:36:38,073
Twelve Jennys, big old warehouse.

965
01:36:38,198 --> 01:36:42,452
We even have hats
that say "Bubba-Gump" on them.

966
01:36:42,577 --> 01:36:45,163
Bubba-Gump Shrimp. A household name.

967
01:36:45,289 --> 01:36:46,999
Hold on there, boy.

968
01:36:47,124 --> 01:36:51,795
Are you telling me you're the owner
of the Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?

969
01:36:51,920 --> 01:36:54,798
Yes. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

970
01:36:54,923 --> 01:37:00,137
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time, but that tops them all.

971
01:37:02,764 --> 01:37:06,226
We were sitting
next to a millionaire.

972
01:37:09,229 --> 01:37:14,318
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

973
01:37:14,443 --> 01:37:19,531
and you tell it so well,
with such enthusiasm.

974
01:37:19,656 --> 01:37:23,619
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

975
01:37:23,744 --> 01:37:26,038
Yes, I would.

976
01:37:30,375 --> 01:37:32,169
That's him right there.

977
01:37:34,296 --> 01:37:37,174
Let me tell you something
about Lieutenant Dan.

978
01:37:43,930 --> 01:37:48,143
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

979
01:38:13,877 --> 01:38:20,133
He never actually said so, but
I think he made his peace with God.

980
01:38:28,016 --> 01:38:29,810
For the second time in 17 days,

981
01:38:29,935 --> 01:38:33,480
President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.

982
01:38:33,605 --> 01:38:38,193
- Base to Jenny 1. Base to Jenny 1.
- Jenny 1. Go, Margo.

983
01:38:38,318 --> 01:38:40,195
Forrest has a phone call.

984
01:38:40,320 --> 01:38:42,781
Well, you'll have to tell them
to call him back.

985
01:38:42,906 --> 01:38:47,411
- He is indisposed at the moment.
- His mama's sick.

986
01:39:06,179 --> 01:39:09,308
- Where's Mama?
- She's upstairs.

987
01:39:11,393 --> 01:39:13,520
Hi, Forrest.

988
01:39:13,645 --> 01:39:17,190
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- All right.

989
01:39:23,697 --> 01:39:27,326
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

990
01:39:38,670 --> 01:39:42,924
- What's the matter, Mama?
- I'm dying, Forrest.

991
01:39:45,385 --> 01:39:48,263
Come on in, sit down over here.

992
01:40:01,902 --> 01:40:08,492
- Why are you dying, Mama?
- It's my time. It's just my time.

993
01:40:10,410 --> 01:40:14,581
Now, don't you be afraid, sweetheart.

994
01:40:16,375 --> 01:40:21,505
Death is just a part of life.
Something we're all destined to do.

995
01:40:22,756 --> 01:40:28,011
I didn't know it,
but I was destined to be your mama.

996
01:40:28,136 --> 01:40:32,766
- I did the best I could.
- You did good.

997
01:40:32,891 --> 01:40:38,772
Well, I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

998
01:40:39,272 --> 01:40:43,819
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

999
01:40:47,322 --> 01:40:49,908
What's my destiny, Mama?

1000
01:40:50,033 --> 01:40:54,454
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1001
01:40:55,831 --> 01:40:58,750
Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.

1002
01:40:58,875 --> 01:41:01,712
You never know
what you're going to get.

1003
01:41:01,837 --> 01:41:06,049
Mama always had a way of explaining
things so I could understand them.

1004
01:41:06,174 --> 01:41:08,176
I will miss you, Forrest.

1005
01:41:09,886 --> 01:41:14,141
She had got the cancer
and died on a Tuesday.

1006
01:41:14,266 --> 01:41:18,937
I bought her a new hat
with little flowers on it.

1007
01:41:22,065 --> 01:41:25,152
And that's all
I have to say about that.

1008
01:41:31,867 --> 01:41:34,703
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number seven bus?

1009
01:41:34,828 --> 01:41:37,998
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1010
01:41:40,917 --> 01:41:45,339
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1011
01:41:45,464 --> 01:41:48,383
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1012
01:41:48,508 --> 01:41:52,346
and a college graduate, the city
fathers of Greenbow, Alabama,

1013
01:41:52,471 --> 01:41:55,140
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1014
01:41:56,808 --> 01:41:59,978
So I never went back
to work for Lieutenant Dan,

1015
01:42:00,103 --> 01:42:02,856
though he did take care
of my Bubba-Gump money.

1016
01:42:02,981 --> 01:42:07,361
He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.

1017
01:42:07,486 --> 01:42:11,114
I got a call from him saying we don't
have to worry about money no more,

1018
01:42:11,239 --> 01:42:15,577
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1019
01:42:17,579 --> 01:42:21,667
Now Mama said there's only
so much fortune a man really needs,

1020
01:42:21,792 --> 01:42:25,128
and the rest is just for showing off.

1021
01:42:25,253 --> 01:42:30,759
So I gave a whole bunch of it
to the Foursquare Gospel Church.

1022
01:42:31,551 --> 01:42:36,556
And I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre fishing hospital.

1023
01:42:38,100 --> 01:42:43,897
And even though Bubba was dead
and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,

1024
01:42:44,022 --> 01:42:47,818
I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.

1025
01:42:50,195 --> 01:42:51,822
You know what?

1026
01:42:51,947 --> 01:42:55,909
She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.

1027
01:42:56,034 --> 01:42:58,495
That smells wonderful.

1028
01:42:58,620 --> 01:43:03,959
And 'cause I was a goZillionaire
and I liked doing it so much,

1029
01:43:04,042 --> 01:43:06,169
I cut that grass for free.

1030
01:43:08,880 --> 01:43:12,384
But at night-time
when there was nothing to do

1031
01:43:12,509 --> 01:43:17,514
and the house was all empty,
I'd always think of Jenny.

1032
01:44:21,495 --> 01:44:24,915
And then, she was there.

1033
01:44:57,990 --> 01:45:01,702
- Hello, Forrest.
- Hello, Jenny.

1034
01:45:12,504 --> 01:45:15,549
Jenny came back and stayed with me.

1035
01:45:15,674 --> 01:45:20,470
Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,

1036
01:45:20,595 --> 01:45:24,516
or maybe it was because she was
so tired, 'cause she went to bed

1037
01:45:24,641 --> 01:45:29,229
and slept and slept,
like she hadn't slept in years.

1038
01:45:29,980 --> 01:45:32,149
It was wonderful having her home.

1039
01:45:32,274 --> 01:45:38,780
Every day we'd take a walk, and l'd
jabber on like a monkey in a tree,

1040
01:45:38,905 --> 01:45:41,742
and she'd listen about
ping-ponging and shrimping

1041
01:45:41,867 --> 01:45:45,787
and Mama making a trip up to heaven.
I did all the talking.

1042
01:45:45,912 --> 01:45:49,291
Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.

1043
01:46:28,914 --> 01:46:31,750
How could you do this?

1044
01:47:08,912 --> 01:47:13,417
Sometimes I guess there
Just aren't enough rocks.

1045
01:47:13,542 --> 01:47:19,381
I never really knew
why she came back, but I didn't care.

1046
01:47:19,506 --> 01:47:24,219
It was like olden times.
We was like peas and carrots again.

1047
01:47:25,679 --> 01:47:29,766
Every day, I'd pick pretty flowers
and put them in her room for her,

1048
01:47:32,060 --> 01:47:36,565
and she gave me the best gift anyone
could ever get in the wide world.

1049
01:47:36,690 --> 01:47:38,692
They're just for running.

1050
01:47:42,446 --> 01:47:45,574
And she even showed me how to dance.

1051
01:47:55,500 --> 01:47:59,546
Well, we was like family,
Jenny and me...

1052
01:48:02,466 --> 01:48:05,761
and it was the happiest time
in my life.

1053
01:48:30,077 --> 01:48:34,081
You done watching it?
I'm going to bed.

1054
01:48:45,008 --> 01:48:47,302
Will you marry me?

1055
01:48:51,515 --> 01:48:54,893
I'd make a good husband, Jenny.

1056
01:48:57,521 --> 01:48:59,439
You would, Forrest.

1057
01:49:01,441 --> 01:49:03,652
But you won't marry me.

1058
01:49:05,612 --> 01:49:08,407
You don't want to marry me.

1059
01:49:11,535 --> 01:49:13,912
Why don't you love me, Jenny?

1060
01:49:19,167 --> 01:49:25,048
I'm not a smart man,
but I know what love is.

1061
01:50:05,839 --> 01:50:08,759
Forrest, I do love you.

1062
01:51:00,894 --> 01:51:06,316
- Where are you running off to?
- I'm not running.

1063
01:52:36,949 --> 01:52:42,496
That day, for no particular reason,
I decided to go for a little run.

1064
01:52:42,955 --> 01:52:46,708
So I ran to the end of the road,
and when I got there

1065
01:52:46,833 --> 01:52:49,503
I thought maybe I'd run
to the end of town.

1066
01:52:49,586 --> 01:52:52,381
President Carter,
suffering from heat exhaustion...

1067
01:52:52,506 --> 01:52:54,257
And when I got there,

1068
01:52:54,383 --> 01:52:58,512
I thought maybe I'd just
run across Greenbow County.

1069
01:52:58,637 --> 01:53:01,098
Now, thinking since I'd run this far,

1070
01:53:01,223 --> 01:53:05,018
maybe I'd just run across
the great state of Alabama.

1071
01:53:05,143 --> 01:53:08,772
And that's what I did.
I ran clear across Alabama.

1072
01:53:08,897 --> 01:53:12,526
No particular reason.
I just kept on going.

1073
01:53:13,318 --> 01:53:15,362
I ran clear to the ocean.

1074
01:53:20,951 --> 01:53:25,038
And when I got there,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1075
01:53:25,163 --> 01:53:28,333
might as well turn around,
just keep on going.

1076
01:53:31,878 --> 01:53:36,258
And when I got to another ocean,
I figured since I'd gone this far,

1077
01:53:38,385 --> 01:53:41,930
I might as well just turn back
and keep right on going.

1078
01:53:42,055 --> 01:53:47,519
When I got tired, I slept.
When I got hungry, I ate.

1079
01:53:47,644 --> 01:53:53,233
When I had to go...
you know... I went.

1080
01:53:53,817 --> 01:53:59,239
- And so, you just ran.
- Yeah.

1081
01:54:35,067 --> 01:54:40,906
I'd think a lot about Mama
and Bubba and Lieutenant Dan.

1082
01:54:41,031 --> 01:54:47,204
But most of all, I thought about
Jenny. I thought about her a lot.

1083
01:54:48,914 --> 01:54:52,584
For more than two years,
a man named Forrest Gump,

1084
01:54:52,709 --> 01:54:55,379
a gardener from Greenbow, Alabama,
stopping only to sleep,

1085
01:54:55,462 --> 01:54:59,841
has been running across America.
Charles Cooper reports.

1086
01:54:59,967 --> 01:55:03,178
For the fourth time
on his journey across America,

1087
01:55:03,303 --> 01:55:08,058
Forrest Gump the gardener will cross
the Mississippi River again today.

1088
01:55:09,518 --> 01:55:13,021
- I'll be damned. Forrest?
- Why are you running?

1089
01:55:13,146 --> 01:55:16,650
- Are you doing this for world peace?
- For the homeless?

1090
01:55:16,775 --> 01:55:19,653
- Are you running for women's rights?
- The environment?

1091
01:55:19,778 --> 01:55:24,658
They couldn't believe somebody would
do all that running for no reason.

1092
01:55:24,783 --> 01:55:29,037
- Why are you doing this?
- I just felt like running.

1093
01:55:29,162 --> 01:55:30,706
I just felt like runnin'.

1094
01:55:31,999 --> 01:55:35,419
It's you.
I can't believe it's really you.

1095
01:55:35,544 --> 01:55:41,008
For some reason, what I was doing
seemed to make sense to people.

1096
01:55:41,133 --> 01:55:43,510
It was like an alarm
went off in my head.

1097
01:55:43,635 --> 01:55:47,222
I said, "Here's a guy
that's got his act together.

1098
01:55:47,347 --> 01:55:51,226
"Here's somebody who has the answer."
I'll follow you anywhere, Mr Gump.

1099
01:55:51,351 --> 01:55:53,604
So I got company.

1100
01:55:55,188 --> 01:56:01,194
And after that, I got more company.
And then, even more people joined in.

1101
01:56:03,405 --> 01:56:06,491
Somebody later told me
it gave people hope.

1102
01:56:09,995 --> 01:56:11,997
I don't know anything about that,

1103
01:56:12,122 --> 01:56:16,627
but some of those people asked me
if I could help them out.

1104
01:56:16,752 --> 01:56:21,214
I was wondering if you might help me.
I'm in the bumper sticker business.

1105
01:56:21,340 --> 01:56:24,801
I need a good slogan, and since
you've been so inspirational,

1106
01:56:24,926 --> 01:56:27,429
I thought
you might be able to help me...

1107
01:56:27,554 --> 01:56:31,683
Whoa, man! You just ran
through a big pile of dog shit!

1108
01:56:32,976 --> 01:56:36,980
- It happens.
- What, shit?

1109
01:56:37,105 --> 01:56:38,899
Sometimes.

1110
01:56:40,776 --> 01:56:44,237
And some years later, I heard
that that fella did come up

1111
01:56:44,363 --> 01:56:48,742
with a bumper sticker slogan
and made a lot of money off of it.

1112
01:56:48,867 --> 01:56:51,119
Another time, I was running along,

1113
01:56:51,244 --> 01:56:53,956
somebody who'd lost all his money
in the t-shirt business,

1114
01:56:54,081 --> 01:56:57,376
he wanted to put my face
on a t-shirt,

1115
01:56:57,501 --> 01:57:01,380
but he couldn't draw that well,
and he didn't have a camera.

1116
01:57:01,505 --> 01:57:05,008
Here, use this one.
Nobody likes that colour anyway.

1117
01:57:09,179 --> 01:57:10,973
Have a nice day.

1118
01:57:12,808 --> 01:57:16,186
Some years later,
I found out that that man did come up

1119
01:57:16,311 --> 01:57:20,232
with an idea for a t-shirt.
He made a lot of money.

1120
01:57:22,776 --> 01:57:27,656
Anyway, like I was saying,
I had a lot of company.

1121
01:57:27,781 --> 01:57:34,288
Mama always said, "Put the past
behind you before you can move on."

1122
01:57:34,788 --> 01:57:38,667
And I think
that's what my running was all about.

1123
01:57:40,168 --> 01:57:46,425
I had run for three years,
two months, 14 days and 16 hours.

1124
01:58:02,190 --> 01:58:04,401
Quiet. Quiet.
He's going to say something.

1125
01:58:16,163 --> 01:58:18,498
I'm pretty tired.

1126
01:58:20,876 --> 01:58:23,253
Think I'll go home now.

1127
01:58:40,771 --> 01:58:43,273
Now what are we supposed to do?

1128
01:58:44,566 --> 01:58:49,488
And just like that,
my runnin' days was over.

1129
01:58:49,613 --> 01:58:51,823
So I went home to Alabama.

1130
01:58:53,617 --> 01:58:57,913
Moments ago, at 2.25 p.m., as
President Reagan was leaving the...

1131
01:58:59,957 --> 01:59:03,919
..five or six gunshots were fired
by an unknown would-be assassin.

1132
01:59:04,044 --> 01:59:06,296
The President was shot
in the chest...

1133
01:59:06,421 --> 01:59:08,215
I picked up the mail.

1134
01:59:08,340 --> 01:59:12,928
And one day, out of the blue clear
sky, I got a letter from Jenny

1135
01:59:13,053 --> 01:59:16,848
wondering if I could come down
to Savannah and see her,

1136
01:59:16,974 --> 01:59:19,017
and that's what I'm doing here.

1137
01:59:20,394 --> 01:59:22,437
She saw me on Tv, running.

1138
01:59:22,562 --> 01:59:26,942
I'm supposed to go on the number nine
bus to Richmond Street

1139
01:59:27,067 --> 01:59:33,907
and get off and go one block left
to 1947 Henry Street, apartment 4.

1140
01:59:34,032 --> 01:59:37,494
Why, you don't need to take a bus.

1141
01:59:37,619 --> 01:59:42,624
Henry Street is just five
or six blocks down that way.

1142
01:59:43,625 --> 01:59:46,545
- Down that way?
- Down that way.

1143
01:59:48,422 --> 01:59:50,841
It was nice talking to you.

1144
01:59:53,176 --> 01:59:55,554
I hope everything works out for you!

1145
02:00:07,024 --> 02:00:11,695
- How you doin'? Come in! Come in!
- I got your letter.

1146
02:00:11,820 --> 02:00:17,784
- I was wondering about that.
- This your house?

1147
02:00:17,909 --> 02:00:20,954
Yeah. It's messy right now.
I just got off work.

1148
02:00:21,079 --> 02:00:24,875
It's nice. You got air conditioning.

1149
02:00:31,048 --> 02:00:34,384
- Thank you.
- I ate some.

1150
02:00:36,470 --> 02:00:42,559
I kept a scrapbook of your clippings,
and everything. There you are.

1151
02:00:44,436 --> 02:00:46,396
And this, I got you running.

1152
02:00:48,815 --> 02:00:53,528
I ran a long way. It's a long time.

1153
02:00:56,031 --> 02:00:58,116
And there...

1154
02:01:04,039 --> 02:01:07,626
Listen, Forrest,
I don't know how to say this.

1155
02:01:10,003 --> 02:01:15,634
I just I want to apologise
for anything that I ever did to you

1156
02:01:15,759 --> 02:01:19,721
'cause I was messed up
for a long time, and...

1157
02:01:23,350 --> 02:01:26,144
- Hi.
- Hey, you.

1158
02:01:26,270 --> 02:01:29,314
- This is an old friend from Alabama.
- How do you do?

1159
02:01:29,523 --> 02:01:32,943
Next week my schedule changes,
so I can...

1160
02:01:33,068 --> 02:01:35,320
No problem. Got to go.
I'm double-parked.

1161
02:01:35,445 --> 02:01:37,281
OK. Thanks.

1162
02:01:39,074 --> 02:01:42,911
This is my very good friend Mr Gump.
Can you say hi?

1163
02:01:43,036 --> 02:01:45,455
- Hello, Mr Gump.
- Hello.

1164
02:01:45,580 --> 02:01:49,584
- Can I go watch Tv now?
- Yes. Just keep it low.

1165
02:01:51,837 --> 02:01:55,007
- You're a mama, Jenny.
- I'm a mama.

1166
02:01:58,385 --> 02:02:02,180
- His name's Forrest.
- Like me!

1167
02:02:04,516 --> 02:02:09,354
- I named him after his daddy.
- He got a daddy named Forrest, too?

1168
02:02:11,023 --> 02:02:13,442
You're his daddy, Forrest.

1169
02:02:30,167 --> 02:02:33,629
Forrest, look at me.
Look at me, Forrest.

1170
02:02:35,005 --> 02:02:40,886
There's nothing you need to do.
You didn't do anything wrong. OK?

1171
02:02:45,515 --> 02:02:47,309
Isn't he beautiful?

1172
02:02:48,644 --> 02:02:52,773
He's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

1173
02:02:55,692 --> 02:02:57,486
But...

1174
02:03:00,656 --> 02:03:02,824
Is he smart? Can he...

1175
02:03:02,950 --> 02:03:07,496
He's very smart. He's one
of the smartest in his class.

1176
02:03:16,004 --> 02:03:18,757
Yeah, it's OK. Go talk to him.

1177
02:03:28,016 --> 02:03:31,561
- What are you watching?
- Bert and Ernie.

1178
02:03:54,042 --> 02:03:58,463
Forrest, I'm sick.

1179
02:04:01,049 --> 02:04:04,511
What, do you have
a cough due to a cold?

1180
02:04:04,636 --> 02:04:09,891
I have some virus, and the doctors,
they don't know what it is,

1181
02:04:10,017 --> 02:04:13,145
and there isn't
anything they can do about it.

1182
02:04:18,025 --> 02:04:20,527
You could come home with me.

1183
02:04:23,030 --> 02:04:28,160
You and little Forrest could
come stay at my house in Greenbow.

1184
02:04:31,622 --> 02:04:34,666
I'll take care of you if you're sick.

1185
02:04:36,209 --> 02:04:38,962
Would you marry me, Forrest?

1186
02:04:44,301 --> 02:04:45,677
OK.

1187
02:04:47,429 --> 02:04:48,930
Please take your seats.

1188
02:04:52,434 --> 02:04:55,437
Forrest? It's time to start.

1189
02:05:14,247 --> 02:05:17,584
Hi. Your tie.

1190
02:05:30,555 --> 02:05:32,808
Lieutenant Dan.

1191
02:05:47,614 --> 02:05:51,618
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hello, Forrest.

1192
02:05:52,035 --> 02:05:55,831
You got new legs. New legs!

1193
02:05:57,165 --> 02:06:00,919
Yeah. I got new legs. Custom-made.

1194
02:06:01,044 --> 02:06:05,340
Titanium alloy. It's what they use
on the space shuttle.

1195
02:06:08,760 --> 02:06:10,762
Magic legs.

1196
02:06:12,639 --> 02:06:17,102
This is my fiancee, Susan.

1197
02:06:19,605 --> 02:06:24,318
- Lieutenant Dan.
- Hi, Forrest.

1198
02:06:24,443 --> 02:06:31,617
- Lieutenant Dan, this is my Jenny.
- Hi. It's nice to meet you finally.

1199
02:06:42,210 --> 02:06:46,256
Do you, Forrest, take Jenny
to be your wife?

1200
02:06:48,008 --> 02:06:52,137
Do you, Jenny,
take Forrest to be your husband?

1201
02:06:53,805 --> 02:06:57,184
And so I pronounce you man and wife.

1202
02:07:28,006 --> 02:07:30,926
- Hey.
- Hi.

1203
02:07:50,028 --> 02:07:52,614
Were you scared in vietnam?

1204
02:07:53,991 --> 02:07:58,495
Yes. Well, I don't know.

1205
02:07:59,663 --> 02:08:05,127
Sometimes it would stop raining long
enough for the stars to come out.

1206
02:08:08,005 --> 02:08:09,923
And then it was nice.

1207
02:08:13,343 --> 02:08:17,806
It was like just before the sun
goes to bed down on the bayou.

1208
02:08:17,931 --> 02:08:22,811
There was always
a million sparkles on the water.

1209
02:08:24,479 --> 02:08:28,191
Like that mountain lake.
It was so clear, Jenny,

1210
02:08:28,317 --> 02:08:33,655
it looked like there were two skies
one on top of the other.

1211
02:08:35,324 --> 02:08:38,744
And then in the desert,
when the sun comes up,

1212
02:08:41,747 --> 02:08:48,170
I couldn't tell where heaven stopped
and the earth began.

1213
02:08:49,630 --> 02:08:51,882
It was so beautiful.

1214
02:08:56,136 --> 02:08:59,014
I wish I could've been there
with you.

1215
02:09:02,309 --> 02:09:04,269
You were.

1216
02:09:14,446 --> 02:09:16,239
I love you.

1217
02:09:20,285 --> 02:09:23,413
You died on a Saturday morning.

1218
02:09:25,290 --> 02:09:29,419
And I had you placed
here under our tree.

1219
02:09:33,882 --> 02:09:39,596
And I had that house of your father's
bulldoZed to the ground.

1220
02:09:43,433 --> 02:09:50,607
Mama always said
that dyin' was a part of life.

1221
02:09:53,902 --> 02:09:56,113
I sure wish it wasn't.

1222
02:09:59,074 --> 02:10:03,245
Little Forrest is doing just fine.

1223
02:10:06,290 --> 02:10:08,834
About to start school again soon,

1224
02:10:09,876 --> 02:10:14,172
and I make his breakfast,
lunch, and dinner every day.

1225
02:10:16,049 --> 02:10:22,222
I make sure he combs his hair
and brushes his teeth every day.

1226
02:10:24,891 --> 02:10:30,981
Teaching him how to play ping-pong.
He's really good.

1227
02:10:31,106 --> 02:10:33,108
Forrest, you go.

1228
02:10:37,904 --> 02:10:40,073
We fish a lot.

1229
02:10:43,452 --> 02:10:47,247
And every night, we read a book.
He's so smart, Jenny.

1230
02:10:49,666 --> 02:10:54,671
You'd be so proud of him. I am.

1231
02:10:56,089 --> 02:10:59,134
He wrote you a letter.

1232
02:11:00,719 --> 02:11:02,804
And he says I can't read it.

1233
02:11:02,930 --> 02:11:06,934
I'm not supposed to,
so I'll just leave it here for you.

1234
02:11:29,706 --> 02:11:35,754
I don't know if mama was right
or if it's Lieutenant Dan.

1235
02:11:36,713 --> 02:11:43,553
I don't know if
we each have a destiny,

1236
02:11:43,679 --> 02:11:50,435
or if we're all just floating around
accidental-like on a breeZe.

1237
02:11:54,898 --> 02:11:59,861
But I think maybe it's both.

1238
02:12:04,700 --> 02:12:07,953
Maybe both is happening
at the same time.

1239
02:12:13,667 --> 02:12:15,585
But I miss you, Jenny.

1240
02:12:22,050 --> 02:12:26,722
If there's anything you need,
I won't be far away.

1241
02:13:01,673 --> 02:13:05,469
Here's your bus. OK.

1242
02:13:07,596 --> 02:13:09,556
I know this.

1243
02:13:09,681 --> 02:13:12,434
I'm gonna share that for
show-and-tell

1244
02:13:12,559 --> 02:13:15,270
because Grandma
used to read it to you.

1245
02:13:15,395 --> 02:13:17,397
My favourite book.

1246
02:13:24,613 --> 02:13:26,865
Here you go.

1247
02:13:33,914 --> 02:13:35,332
Don't...

1248
02:13:37,542 --> 02:13:42,714
- I want to tell you I love you.
- I love you, too, Daddy.

1249
02:13:42,839 --> 02:13:46,009
I'll be right here when you get back.

1250
02:13:50,555 --> 02:13:54,935
You understand this is
the bus to school, don't you?

1251
02:13:55,060 --> 02:13:59,856
Of course, and you're Dorothy Harris,
and I'm Forrest Gump.



